Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.level

Class Percent

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.level.Percent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Percent>
public final class Percent extends Object implements Comparable<Percent>
A percentage of any range (not only from 0 to 100%). A percent object can be created with percent(double), passing in a percentage, like 50 or 90 to get 50% or 90%.

Operations

  • dividedBy(double) - This percentage divided by the given value
  • inverse() - This percentage's distance from 100%
  • minus(Percent) - This percentage minus the given percentage
  • plus(Percent) - This percentage plus the given percentage
  • scale(double) - The given value scaled by this percentage
  • scale(int) - The given value scaled by this percentage
  • scale(long) - The given value scaled by this percentage
  • times(double) - This percentage times the given percentage

Conversions

  • asInt() - This percentage rounded to an int value
  • asUnitValue() - This percentage as a parametric value (divided by 100.0)
  • asZeroToOne() - This value as a unit value between 0 and 1, inclusive
